10
1. Sales Strategy & Revenue Ownership

Drive sales performance and ensure achievement of revenue, gross margin, and productivity (sales/sq. ft.) targets for all stores in the NCR region. 
Execute regional sales strategies aligned with overall brand objectives and seasonal campaigns. 
Identify high-potential micro-markets and drive expansion through targeted store openings and localized marketing.


2. Store Launches & Expansion

Identify and evaluate potential store locations based on market opportunity, catchment demographics, and competitor presence.
Oversee end-to-end store launch process including site readiness, merchandising, staffing, and opening readiness.
Collaborate cross-functionally with marketing, VM, and operations to ensure a successful go-live and steady state operations.


3. Team Leadership & Development

Hire, train, and manage store managers and sales executives across all stores in the region.
Conduct regular performance reviews and implement coaching interventions to improve productivity.
Facilitate functional and behavioral training as per the training calendar to build strong product knowledge, selling skills, and customer orientation.
Foster a culture of accountability, customer focus, and high performance within the sales team.
4. Merchandising, Inventory & Store Operations

Optimize display stock and back-store inventory to increase stock turns and reduce holding costs.
Ensure effective visual merchandising, product labels, updated pricing, promotional offers, and POS materials are implemented as per brand guidelines.
Manage day-to-day sales transactions, returns, refunds, and ensure timely customer order fulfillment.


5. Market Intelligence & Competitive Benchmarking

Conduct ongoing market surveillance across competitor retailers for product mix, pricing, promotional offers, and visual merchandising standards.
Track customer footfall, conversion, and category trends to inform marketing and merchandising strategies.
Provide inputs for product demand forecasting and inventory planning based on sales trends and consumer insights.
6. Financial & Operational Excellence

Manage regional sales budgets and expenditures to ensure cost efficiency and profitability.
Implement measures to increase margins and minimize store-level expenses without compromising customer experience.
Track KPIs such as revenue per store, sales per sq. ft., inventory turns, customer conversion, and team productivity.
